====Usage====
*The name applied to the language spoken in Iran is a matter of considerable controversy.  A nationalistic Iranian emigrant community puts forth the insistent point of view that a single language called Persian is spoken in all three primary countries.  This view does not appear to predominate among people from the other two countries, whose emigrant communities are much smaller.  There is a growing tendency among non-Iranians to refer to the official language of Iran as Western Farsi or more often simply Farsi.  Similarly the Eastern Farsi or Persian of Western Afghanistan is referred to as [[Dari]] and the version of the language spoken in Tajikistan is known as Tajik.
